1 B. C. When a nominee or electee is to be selected by lot
2 pursuant to the provisions of this section, the following procedures
3 shall be observed:
4 1. The secretary of the appropriate election board shall, on or
5 before the tenth day following the second election, notify each of
6 the tying candidates for which the vote was tied. The notice shall
7 include the time, date and location of the selection, shall be made
8 in writing by registered or certified mail and shall be postmarked
9 not fewer than five (5) days prior to the meeting;
10 2. A candidate may designate one person as a witness to attend
11 the meeting on the candidate's behalf. The designation shall be
12 made in writing, signed by the candidate and presented to the
13 secretary of the appropriate election board;
14 3. The secretary of the appropriate election board shall, in
15 full view of those present at the meeting, clearly write or print
16 the name of each tied candidate on separate pieces of paper
17 measuring approximately equal size. The names of the candidates
18 shall be written or printed on the same color and type of paper.
19 The papers shall be folded in half one time so that the written
20 names are not visible and shall be placed into a container selected
21 by the secretary of the appropriate election board;
22 4. The secretary shall draw, or may designate a person other
23 than the candidates, witnesses or other person directly interested
24 in the election to draw, one paper, and the name of the nominee or
